                        <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8">
                            I've been supported by the <span class="font-juana font-semibold text-secondary">Ruby on Rails</span> community since I first ran <code class="text-accent">rails g new</code> on my computer. 
                            The Odin Project (among many free online resources) helped me teach myself how to code from the-ground-up. In 2023 alone, I got to <span class="text-primary">attend RailsConf</span> (ty @RubyCentral), coded a project for the <span class="text-primary">Rails Hackathon</span>, and also got <span class="text-primary">paid to code</span> for the first time (beginnerbounties.com)!
                        </p>
                        <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8">
                            I've always been a freelancer in my professional career, including running a real-estate photography business, and now a couple of small coding gigs.
                            </br>
                            Now, I'm looking for <span class="text-green-400 font-juana font-bold">a full-time position</span>.
                        </p>
